The former. I got the chords part, but the notion of loading and unloading the dishes being “dissonant” chores (either individually, or as a pair in relation to each other) just didn’t activate any intuitions for me.

At this point, I guess I get it — the chores produce noises that could be described as dissonant, in the sense of being harsh/jarring/unpleasant. It seems a little stretchy to me, but I still like the theme :)

@Barry Ancona,

Thank you so much for providing this link. I had done that first puzzle and looked at it again. I had no idea what the revealer was getting at today until I read the Wordplay. I would highly recommend reading that column today. Mr. Steinberg talks at length about how he came up with the theme and his interaction with Will Shortz. 

If you didn’t catch it from the Constructor Notes today, David Steinberg was at the tender age of *14* when he had his crossword puzzle published in the New York Times. What were you accomplishing at that age? 😄

